<chapter xml:id="primitive-types-and-variables" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Variables, primitive types, and expressions</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      This unit introduces the lowest level elements of the Java programming
      language: the two numeric <term>primitive types</term> you need to know
      for the AP exam; <term>variables</term>, which allow us to give names to
      important values in our programs; arithmetic <term>expressions</term> that
      allow us to write programs that do math, and various <term>assignment
      operators</term> that allow us to give values to our variables.
    </p>
  </introduction>

